Texts.Chs: 展出的一箱保存完好的昆虫。讨厌。
Texts.Eng: A case of preserved insects on display. Yuck.

Texts.Chs: 一个详细的，如果是病态的，昆虫展示柜。为你的青蛙人朋友准备一份自助餐！
Texts.Eng: A detailed, if morbid, insect display case. Doubles as a smorgasbord for your Frögg friends!

Texts.Chs: 我毫不怀疑，科技发展部的科学家会毫不犹豫地展示他们以前的“病人”。
Texts.Eng: I've no doubt Miniknog scientists wouldn't hesitate to display their former "patients" like this.
Little bugs can't flutter away like this.

Texts.Chs: 伙计，我希望他们被塞进里面的时候不是活着的。
Texts.Eng: Man, I hope they weren't alive when they were stuffed in there.

Texts.Chs: 近距离观察这些昆虫翅膀的结构非常迷人。
Texts.Eng: The structure of these insects wings are rather fascinating when observed up close.

Texts.Chs: 昆虫翅膀的结构有一种特殊的美。
Texts.Eng: There's a particular beauty in the structure of insect wings.

Texts.Chs: 这对虫子来说有点可怕，不是吗？
Texts.Eng: This is a tad macabre for the bugs, no?
